How to build and run the project
================================

Under Linux:
------------
EXAMPLE 1 (default parameters, release version):

cd build
cmake ..
make -j
cd ..
mpirun -np 4 ./cavity3d


EXAMPLE 2 (use clang compiler, compile debug version):

cd build
cmake ..
CXX=/usr/bin/clang++ cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug ..
cd ..
mpirun -np 4 ./cavity3d


EXAMPLE 3 (using the CMake GUI):

- Execute the command "cmake-gui"
- Specify "Where is the source code" to be the cavity3d example directory
- Specify "Where to build the binaries" to be the cavity3d/build directory
- Click on "Configure", and on "Finish" (Instead of the default "Unix
  Makefiles" option, you may want to select another one, like "CodeBlocks -
  Unix Makefiles" to produce a configuration file for your a given IDE)
- Click on Generate
- Close cmake-gui
- Execute the following:
cd build
make -j
cd ..
mpirun -np 4 ./cavity3d

Under Windows:
--------------
- run cmake
- Specify "Where is the source code" to be the cavity3d example directory
- Specify "Where to build the binaries" to be the cavity3d/build directory
- Click on "Configure", and on "Finish"
- Click on Generate
- Close cmake
- In the file explorer, double click on the generated solution file, which
  should start Microsoft Visual Studio.
- Click on "build"
